                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/23.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 20. You will continue to make earnest protest against attempts to
                    extort forced loans from foreigners. Advise persons who may be compelled to
                    comply with demands for money to obtain receipts for amounts paid. Report to
                    Department all such cases coming to your attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
